  "content_id": "1bc01d54-398b-4470-8814-73dbd5a56ad0",
  "description": "If your business provides a tool allowance to employees - what you must report to HMRC ",
  "details": {
    "external_related_links": [

    ],
    "hide_chapter_navigation": false,
    "parts": [
      {
        "body": "<p>As an employer providing a tool allowance to your employees, you have certain tax, National Insurance and reporting obligations.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"whats-included\">What’s included</h2>\n\n<p>A tool allowance is a payment you give to an employee to buy tools that are only used for work.</p>\n\n",
        "slug": "overview",
        "title": "Overview"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>Some tool allowances are covered by <a href=\"/employer-reporting-expenses-benefits/dispensations\">exemptions</a> (which have replaced dispensations). This means you won’t have to include them in your end-of-year reports.</p>\n\n<p>If you don’t have an exemption, you must <a href=\"/employer-reporting-expenses-benefits/reporting-and-paying\">report the allowance on form P11D</a>.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"if-work-tools-are-available-for-employees-to-use-privately\">If work tools are available for employees to use privately</h2>\n\n<p>The allowance you provide counts as earnings. You must:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>add the amount to the employee’s other earnings</li>\n  <li>deduct and pay <abbr title=\"Pay as you earn\">PAYE</abbr> tax and Class 1 National Insurance through payroll</li>\n</ul>\n\n",
        "slug": "what-to-report-and-pay",
        "title": "What to report and pay"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>The following guides contain more detailed information:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/nimmanual/nim06230.htm\">Class 1 National Insurance: expenses and allowances - tool allowances</a></p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/eimanual/eim21610.htm\">particular benefits: accommodation, supplies and services on the employer’s premises</a></p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n",
        "slug": "technical-guidance",
        "title": "Technical guidance"
      }
    ]
  },
